articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Rep. Houlahan: No regrets about impeachment vote
articles.description: Rep. Chrissy Houlahan (D-PA) tells NBC’s Kasie Hunt she has no regrets about her impeachment vote, but calls it 'one of the hardest things, if not the hardest thing' she’s ever had to do.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Sen. Merkley: 'The whole ‘imminent’ argument is basically made up'
articles.description: Sen Jeff Merkley, (D-OR), a member of the Foreign Relations Committee, says members of the Trump Administration are now trying to 'backfill' the narrative they created about General Qassem Soleimani plotting an 'imminent attack.'

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Rep. Crenshaw: 'When we talk about all the intel out there, I was the guy collecting that intel'
articles.description: Rep. Dan Crenshaw (R-TX), a former Navy SEAL and a member of the Homeland Security Committee, weighs in on the Iran conflict, telling NBC’s Kasie Hunt that his past experience taught him, 'If you're going to have a strategy, you have to do something first, yo…

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Lawmaker on Soleimani strike briefing: 'I can't share anything that was in it, but the point is, there was nothing in it'
articles.description: Veteran and Armed Services Committee member Rep. Anthony Brown (D-MD) tells NBC’s Kasie Hunt that the administration’s briefing on the strike that took out General Qassem Soleimani contained no mention of embassies, as the president suggested this week.
